Title: Title of the dataset following the format  Feature Type/Data Theme, Geographic Coverage, Date
Abstract: Concise descriptive overview of the dataset
Originator(s): Originator of the dataset.  Use Library of Congress Name Authorities listing (http://authorities.loc.gov), if possible
Collection/Series Identification: Name of the collection that the dataset belongs to
Publisher: Name of the publisher.  Use Library of Congress Name Authorities listing (http://authorities.loc.gov), if possible
Publication Date:
Date the dataset was made available for release.
Use YYYY-MM-DD, or "01" if unknown
Date of Content:
Date or, range of dates, that represents the content of the data.
Use YYYY-MM-DD
Use Constraints: Free text rules/recommendations for how the dataset can be used.
Theme Keywords (LCSH): Keywords list based on the Library of Congress Keyword Authorities listing (http://authorities.loc.gov)
Place Keywords (GEOnet):
Keywords following the format and conventions of the GEOnet Names Server
 (http://earth-info.nga/mil/gns/html/index.html)
Feature and Attribute Definitions: Description and details of the critical contents of the dataset (attribute table).  If feature attributes of the dataset or feature attribute values are not self-explanatory, describe them.
